{"title":"Cyclist Magazine Podcast: Phil Burt, the king of bike fit","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/phil-burt-bike-fit-podcast","date":1740047702000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/phil-burt-bike-fit-podcast\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast: Phil Burt, the king of bike fit</a></p>\n\n<p>In this week’s episode of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/cyclist-magazine-podcast\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast</a> James is joined by Phil Burt, former head of physiotherapy at British Cycling and Team Sky and the man who literally wrote <a href=\"https://www.bloomsbury.com/uk/bike-fit-2nd-edition-9781472990105/\" target=\"_blank\">the book on bike fit</a>. They discuss micro adjusters and macro absorbers, how riders’ needs and wants are changing, and the affect of indoor cycling on the body.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Phil also explains the theory behind the use of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/best-crank-length-for-cycling\">shorter cranks</a>, the advantages, and how Bradley Wiggins was already on 165mm cranks at the Rio Olympics in 2016.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Interview starts at 10:38.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Head to <a href=\"https://www.philburtinnovation.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">philburtinnovation.co.uk</a> to find out more about Phil’s work and to make an assessment or bike fit booking.</p>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Listen to <a href=\"https://shows.acast.com/cyclist-magazine-podcast/episodes/125-phil-burt-the-king-of-bike-fit\" target=\"_blank\">Phil Burt on the Cyclist Magazine Podcast now on Acast</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Check out <a href=\"https://shows.acast.com/618e52740da782001471efbe/episodes\" target=\"_blank\">all episodes</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Also available wherever you get your podcasts</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>This episode is brought to you by Trek’s custom Project One programme, which offers full custom paint, components and setup o